@@ -0,0 +1,90 @@
+# P4.9 — latency-contract silence operator policy
+
+P4.9 adds an operator policy layer on top of the P4.7/P4.8 notifier silence workflow.
+
+The goal is to stop the same `purpose` from being re-acked forever without stronger accountability.
+
+## What changes
+
+When an operator runs:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m orderflow_services.latency_contract_deploy_lint_silence_v1 ack \
+  --purpose meta_cov_rollout_controller \
+  --operator alex \
+  --ticket INC-42 \
+  --reason "known drift while fix is in progress" \
+  --minutes 120
+```
+
+P4.9 now enforces a rolling policy window per purpose:
+
+- `LATENCY_CONTRACT_DEPLOY_LINT_SILENCE_POLICY_WINDOW_HOURS`
+- `LATENCY_CONTRACT_DEPLOY_LINT_SILENCE_POLICY_MAX_BUDGET_MINUTES`
+- `LATENCY_CONTRACT_DEPLOY_LINT_SILENCE_POLICY_MAX_ACKS`
+
+If the new ack would exceed either the cumulative silence budget or the ack-count limit, the command is denied unless the operator provides a separate escalation ticket:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m orderflow_services.latency_contract_deploy_lint_silence_v1 ack \
+  --purpose meta_cov_rollout_controller \
+  --operator alex \
+  --ticket INC-42 \
+  --escalation-ticket SEV-9001 \
+  --reason "drift accepted temporarily during incident bridge" \
+  --minutes 120
+```
+
+## Rules
+
+- escalation ticket must be present once policy limits are exceeded
+- escalation ticket must differ from the normal work ticket
+- the same escalation ticket cannot be reused again for the same purpose inside the active policy window
+- denial only affects notifier suppression; rollout gate enforcement is unchanged
+
+## Redis fields
+
+Per-purpose silence hash now also stores:
+
+- `policy_window_start_ts_ms`
+- `policy_window_end_ts_ms`
+- `policy_window_ack_count`
+- `policy_window_budget_minutes_used`
+- `policy_limit_hit_total`
+- `policy_denied_total`
+- `policy_last_limit_kind`
+- `policy_last_deny_reason`
+- `policy_current_override_active`
+- `policy_current_override_ticket`
+- `policy_last_override_ticket`
+
+## Audit events
+
+New events in `ops:latency_contract:events:v1`:
+
+- `latency_deploy_lint_ack_silence_policy_denied`
+- `latency_deploy_lint_ack_silence_policy_override`
+
+## Metrics
+
+- `latency_contract_deploy_lint_silence_policy_window_ack_count{purpose}`
+- `latency_contract_deploy_lint_silence_policy_window_budget_minutes_used{purpose}`
+- `latency_contract_deploy_lint_silence_policy_limit_hit_total{purpose}`
+- `latency_contract_deploy_lint_silence_policy_denied_total{purpose}`
+- `latency_contract_deploy_lint_silence_policy_override_active{purpose}`
+- `latency_contract_deploy_lint_summary_policy_blocked_gate_active_total`
+- `latency_contract_deploy_lint_summary_policy_override_gate_active_total`
+
+## Exit code
+
+Denied ack exits with:
+
+- `LATENCY_CONTRACT_DEPLOY_LINT_SILENCE_POLICY_DENIED_EXIT_CODE` (default `27`)
+
+## Quick checks
+
